# Reflection surfaces use git's built-in union merge driver so that
# concurrent merges combine both sides' appended lines instead of
# conflicting — no committed reflection can be silently dropped (issue
# #398). Source of truth is the per-entry fragments in
# reflections/active/, which never collide; these rules protect the
# generated aggregate and the append-only annual archives.
REFLECTION_LOG.md merge=union
reflections/archive/*.md merge=union
